# Function Guidelines

## Core Principles
- Keep functions small and focused (single responsibility)
- Maximum 20-30 lines per function
- Return early to avoid deep nesting
- Use descriptive names that indicate purpose

## Function Structure
- Use function expressions with `const` rather than declarations
- Use default parameters instead of conditionals when appropriate
- Place helper functions after main functions
- Keep parameter count low (ideally 3 or fewer)

## Documentation
```javascript
/**
 * Example of proper function documentation
 * @param {type} paramName - Parameter description
 * @returns {type} Description of return value
 */
const functionName = function(paramName) {
  // Implementation
};
```

## Error Handling
- Handle edge cases at the start of functions
- Use appropriate error types
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Document expected errors in JSDoc comments

## Testing
- Write tests for both expected and edge cases
- Keep tests independent
- Use descriptive test names
- Test error conditions
